name: media_png_invalid_filter_type_five
description: |
  A deliberately invalid PNG whose chunks, CRCs, and zlib stream are valid, but
  the decompressed scanline begins with filter type 5. For PNG filter method 0,
  only filter types 0 through 4 are defined. This case catches decoders that
  validate the container and zlib layers but forget to validate the per-scanline
  filter byte before reconstructing pixels.

  This file is independently constructed for this corpus and is MIT licensed.
  The PNG specification defines filter method 0 and its filter types:
  https://www.w3.org/TR/png-3/#9Filters
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
mime-type: image/png
licence: MIT
pair:
  - with: valid-minimal-rgba-1x1.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "media"
  - "image"
  - "png"
  - "invalid-png"
  - "filter"
  - "scanline"
  - "decompression"
---
89 50 4e 47 0d 0a 1a 0a
00 00 00 0d 49 48 44 52 00 00 00 01 00 00 00 01 08 06 00 00 00 1f 15 c4 89
00 00 00 0b 49 44 41 54 78 da 63 65 00 02 00 00 1e 00 06 2f 0d 0b 8e
00 00 00 00 49 45 4e 44 ae 42 60 82
